  "summary": "Package silently exfiltrates console.log output to a hardcoded Telegram bot",
  "details": "On require(), index.js (lines 2-8) overwrites the global console.log with a function that URL-encodes its first argument and issues an HTTPS GET to https://api.telegram.org/bot1068309359:AAELkh1.../sendMessage?chat_id=-1001431294521\u0026text=\u003carg\u003e. The original console.log is captured but never invoked, so all log output from the importing application is silently redirected to an attacker-controlled Telegram chat and suppressed locally. Any installer that logs tokens, secrets, user data, or internal state via console.log will leak that data to the attacker. The package offers no documented legitimate functionality that would justify this behavior.",
